<h1>Problem 1664 - 2019 USA TSTST, P2 of 9, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute triangle with circumcircle \(\Omega\) and orthocenter \(H\). Points \(D\) and \(E\) lie on segments \(AB\) and \(AC\) respectively, such that \(AD = AE\). The lines through \(B\) and \(C\) parallel to \(\overline{DE}\) intersect \(\Omega\) again at \(P\) and \(Q\), respectively. Denote by \(\omega\) the circumcircle of \(\triangle ADE\).</p>
<p><ul><li>Show that lines \(PE\) and \(QD\) meet on \(\omega\).</li><li>Prove that if \(\omega\) passes through \(H\), then lines \(PD\) and \(QE\) meet on \(\omega\) as well.</li></ul></p>
